    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Whitfield, Thornbury - Glouc</placeName>
                        <date>Oct 15 1844</date>
                        <salute>Revd Sir</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                  <p>I beg to enclose a specimen of wheat afflicted by a curious disease or at any rate in a curious manner; I send it to you having read the paper by you on the diseases of wheat in the Eng. Ag. Society's Journal. It was sent to me by a person who asks for information on the subject in the Agricl Gazette. And I know nothing about it, never having seen a specimen like it.</p>
                  <p>I should feel greatly obliged by any information that you may be able to give about it.</p>
                  <p>and I am Sir</p>
                  <p>Yours most respectfully</p>
                  <p>John C. Morton</p>                        
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </body>
